This release contains the following products:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Accounting:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Grid-Safe v. 1.3.1&lt;/b&gt; release in SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;This is the first release of the Globus accounting solution in UMD.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Client Tools:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Gfal2 v. 2.4.8&lt;/b&gt; release in both SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;First release of the GFAL 2.0 Utility tools (gfal2-util) in UMD.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Job Execution:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;CREAM SLURM v. 1.0.1&lt;/b&gt; released in both SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is the first release of cream for slurm in UMD.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;CREAM TORQUE v. 2.1.3&lt;/b&gt; released in both SL5 and SL6&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a bugfix release which solves the issue of the information provider failing to parse remote data and the wrong total cpu count from PBS infoprovider together with a dependency issue with lcg-info-dynamic-scheduler.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Job Scheduling:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;WMS v. 3.6.3&lt;/b&gt; released in both SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a bugfix release which solves some issues at both server and client level, namely the fact that the wms job purger was still updating the wms's proxy with 512bits proxies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Other:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;DPM-YAIM 4.2.20&lt;/b&gt; released in both SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This new release provides some configuration changes among others at the level of the&amp;nbsp; xroot, http srm plugins.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;GridSite v. 2.2.2&lt;/b&gt; release in SL5&amp;nbsp; SL6 and debian:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This
 is a revision of GridSite, fixing the issue of two or more simultaneous
 (overlapping) delegation operations interfering with each other.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Glexec v. 1.2.2&lt;/b&gt; release in both SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This release of glexec provides some bug-fixes and improvements at the level of both gLExec and lcmaps.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;WN SLURM v. 1.0.0&lt;/b&gt; released in both SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is the first release of cream slurm clients in UMD.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
